{
  "text": "Here \u03b7 = log(t\u2212t 0 ) with the branch cut chosen appropriately, and P i , Q i , R i are polynomials in \u03b7. These polynomials are given explicitly in earlier work [CITATION_1] . Here we note that Q \u22122 = \u2212i/5, R \u22122 = 1/5, P \u22121 = Q \u22121 = 2i, and R \u22121 = 17/9, so that the dominant part of the singularity is a pole for x(t) and a double pole for y(t) and z(t). The first terms in the psi-series which are not constants are",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14924328"
